SHEEP POX & GOAT POX, OVINE - RUSSIA (02): (PRIMORSKY) OIE
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 15 Oct 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2010; 23(42) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9833>


Sheep pox and goat pox, Russia
------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 15 Oct 2010 from Dr Nicolay Vlasov, CVO, Veterinary services, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Moscow, Russia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 27 Sep 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 1 Oct 2010
Report date: 15 Oct 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Oct 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Oct 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Capripoxvirus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Iskra, Chernigovsky, Primorsky Kray [territory]
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Sep 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Species: sheep
Susceptible: 206
Cases: 32
Deaths: 4
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; treatment of affected animals (-)
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Federal Centre for Animal Health (FGI ARRIAH), Yurievets, Vladimir (national laboratory)
Species: sheep
Test: polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date: 1 Oct 2010
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The location of this outbreak is in the very far eastern part of Russia, relatively close to the border of both China and North Korea, and can be seen on the map included in the OIE report at the source URL above and on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/0dW4>.

As indicated in Mod.AS comments in Sheep pox & goat pox, ovine - Russia: (PR) 20101018.3775, previous outbreaks of this disease have occurred in 2002, 2003, and 2008 -- sometimes affecting goats and sometimes affecting sheep. The same capripoxvirus causes both diseases. - Mod.PC]
